  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Equation.}\n\\[\n\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0827}}:\\mathcal{X}_{\\mathrm{id0827}}\\longrightarrow \\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{id0827}},\\qquad\n\\mathcal{N}_{\\mathrm{TRAWIN}}(\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0827}})=\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0827}},\\qquad\n\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0827}}(x)\\in\\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{adm}}.\n\\]\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.} Let $x\\in \\mathcal{X}_{\\mathrm{id0827}}$ be the local coordinate or field sample.  The entry transform is\\[\ny=\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0827}}(x),\\qquad \\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0827}}:\\mathcal{X}_{\\mathrm{id0827}}\\longrightarrow \\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{id0827}}.\n\\]\n\nIts differential transport is represented by the id-local Jacobian\\[\nJ_{0827}(x)=D\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0827}}\\big|_x,\\qquad \\det J_{0827}(x)\\neq 0\n\\]\n\nCompatibility with the Nonary chain is enforced by\\[\n\\mathcal{N}_{\\mathrm{TRAWIN}}(\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0827}})=\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0827}},\\qquad y\\in\\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{adm}}.\n\\]\n\nThus the Nonary derivation for [ID 0827] is the three-stage passage\n\\[\n\\mathcal{X}_{\\mathrm{id0827}}\\xrightarrow{\\,\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0827}}\\,} \\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{id0827}}\\xrightarrow{\\,\\mathcal{N}_{\\mathrm{TRAWIN}}\\,} \\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{adm}},\n\\]\nwith the entry title fixing the meaning of the carrier and the TRAWIN normalization fixing the admissibility test.\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.} SPATIAL CONVOLUTION OF OMEGA is read as a transport rule: it converts local data into an admissible Nonary coordinate while preserving enough differential structure for the following entry to use it.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
  },
